The config command provides a namespace for user-specific preferences. Currently supports one subcommand: `drift config theme NAME` which writes the theme preference to .drift/user-settings.xml (not committed to git; .drift/.gitignore is created by drift init to exclude it). `drift config theme` with no NAME argument prints the current effective theme. Unknown theme names are rejected with an error listing the 12 available themes. Missing the subcommand (e.g. bare `drift config`) returns a usage error. See <ref spec="output.config_theme">config theme</ref> and <ref spec="output_impl.user_settings">user settings</ref>.